HEADWORD: Limbo
<hw>Lim"bo</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧m"b⟦osl⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Jamaican
E. <ets>limba</ets> to bend, fr. E. <ets>limber</ets> (1950)
<au>MW10</au>]</ety> <def>A West Indian dance contest, in which
participants must dance under a pole which is lowered successively until
only one participant can successfully pass under, without falling. It is
often performed at celebrations, such as weddings.</def>⟦br⟧
